        <div n="368A04B2">
          <head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-1">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">While the prosecution for the Drapier's fourth letter was depending, Swift one day waited at the Castle for an audience of Lord Carteret, the Lord Lieutenant, till his patience was exhausted; upon which he wrote the following couplet on a window, and went away:&#13;</l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-2">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-368A04B2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-368A04B2-line-1" n="1">My very good Lord, 'tis a very hard task,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-368A04B2-line-2" n="2">For a man to wait here, who has nothing to ask.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
